antages associated with the fleet management system. However, you should know a right <\/span>fleet management software <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">can open a floodgate of opportunities, such as:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Builds a reporting schedule to keep a strict watch on safety protocols<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ensures drivers and vehicles are following the federal and state regulations to avoid steep penalities<\/span><\/span>&nbsp;<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Predictive analysis reduces downtime due to any maintenance or repair issues<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><em><strong>Now, let\u2019s take a quick look at variety of fleet management systems:<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Condition_Based_Maintenance_CBM\"><\/span><b>Condition Based Maintenance (CBM)<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This type involves vehicles to be integrated with sensors to generate digital reports. Here, sensors share data, which is further utilized by fleet managers to optimize fleet performance which was never experienced before.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It involves real-time vehicle tracking for better operational visibility and taking proactive measures for safer operation execution.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Predictive_Maintenance_PdM\"><\/span><b>Predictive Maintenance (PdM)<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As the name suggests, it is all about a predictive approach to maintain the fleet and get the repairs performed much before it causes the havoc of downtime.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It also ensures cutting down fuel expenditure and ensuring vehicles run at peak efficiency while sharing real-time alerts and achieving quick responses.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Preventive_Maintenance\"><\/span><b>Preventive Maintenance<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Prevention is better than cure!<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And this model fits it well, as it is designed to help fleets reduce downtime through proactive measures.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It imbibes different strategies, such as: regular maintenance checks, high-quality parts, and following the manufacturer&#8217;s guidelines for service and repairs.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This model is especially useful to train drivers and help them follow guidelines for safer travel and address potential issues much before they turn aggressive.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Reactive_Maintenance_RM\"><\/span><b>Reactive Maintenance (RM)<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This model is more about the maintenance being conducted in response to a breakdown or system failure.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Reliability_Centered_Maintenance_RCM\"><\/span><b>Reliability Centered Maintenance (RCM)<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This model gives businesses an opportunity to build an internal maintenance schedule and policy to attain optimal performance, longevity, and safety for their vehicles.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This model is hugely impacted by different factors, such as: terrain, the climate, and more. <\/span><\/p>\n<div class=\"hbblog-cta\" style=\"background: #fdfdfd!important; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 35px 25px 35px 25px; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #dfdfdf; border-radius: 5px; border-bottom-color: #f5bd00; border-bottom-width: 3px!important;\">\